President Barack Obama released a statement expressing his sadness over the passing of Steve Jobs, calling him one of the greatest American innovators. Obama praised Jobs for his ability to think differently, believe he could change the world, and actually do it. He highlighted Jobs' success in building one of the most successful companies, making computers personal, and revolutionizing the information industry. Obama also acknowledged Jobs' talent for storytelling and the joy he brought to millions of people. The President concluded by saying that the world has lost a visionary and that it is a testament to Jobs' success that many learned of his passing on a device he invented. He extended his thoughts and prayers to Jobs' family and loved ones.